#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Māra"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Sattavassānubandhasutta → sattavassasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | sattavassāni (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Sattavassānubandhasutta"
msgstr "24. Seven Years of Following"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.24:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā at the goatherd’s banyan "
"tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

msgctxt "sn4.24:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena māro pāpimā sattavassāni bhagavantaṃ anubandho hoti "
"otārāpekkho otāraṃ alabhamāno."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Māra the Wicked had been following the Buddha for seven "
"years hoping to find a vulnerability without success."

msgctxt "sn4.24:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.123"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.270"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.1"
msgid "“Sokāvatiṇṇo nu vanamhi jhāyasi,"
msgstr "“Are you overwhelmed by sorrow that you meditate in the forest?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.2"
msgid "Vittaṃ nu jīno uda patthayāno;"
msgstr "Have you lost a fortune, or do you long for one?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.3"
msgid "Āguṃ nu gāmasmimakāsi kiñci,"
msgstr "Or perhaps you’ve committed some crime in the village?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.4"
msgid "Kasmā janena na karosi sakkhiṃ;"
msgstr "Why don’t you get too close to people?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:2.5"
msgid "Sakkhī na sampajjati kenaci te”ti."
msgstr "And why does no-one get close to you?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.1"
msgid "“Sokassa mūlaṃ palikhāya sabbaṃ,"
msgstr "“I’ve dug out the root of sorrow completely."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.2"
msgid "Anāgu jhāyāmi asocamāno;"
msgstr "I practice absorption free of guilt or sorrow."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.3"
msgid "Chetvāna sabbaṃ bhavalobhajappaṃ,"
msgstr "I’ve cut off all greed and hunger for future lives."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:3.4"
msgid "Anāsavo jhāyāmi pamattabandhū”ti."
msgstr "Undefiled, I practice absorption, O kinsman of the negligent!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ vadanti mama yidanti,"
msgstr "“The things they call ‘mine’,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.2"
msgid "ye vadanti mamanti ca;"
msgstr "and those who say ‘it’s mine’:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.3"
msgid "Ettha ce te mano atthi,"
msgstr "if your mind remains there,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:4.4"
msgid "na me samaṇa mokkhasī”ti."
msgstr "you won’t escape me, ascetic!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ vadanti na taṃ mayhaṃ,"
msgstr "“The things they speak of aren’t mine;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.2"
msgid "ye vadanti na te ahaṃ;"
msgstr "I’m not someone who speaks like that."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ pāpima jānāhi,"
msgstr "So know this, Wicked One:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:5.4"
msgid "na me maggampi dakkhasī”ti."
msgstr "you won’t even see the path I take.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.271"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.1"
msgid "“Sace maggaṃ anubuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "“If you’ve discovered the path"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.2"
msgid "khemaṃ amatagāminaṃ;"
msgstr "that’s safe, and leads to the deathless,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.3"
msgid "Apehi gaccha tvameveko,"
msgstr "go and walk that path alone—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:6.4"
msgid "kimaññamanusāsasī”ti."
msgstr "why teach it to anyone else?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.1"
msgid "“Amaccudheyyaṃ pucchanti,"
msgstr "“Those crossing to the far shore"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.2"
msgid "ye janā pāragāmino;"
msgstr "ask what’s beyond the domain of Death."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.3"
msgid "Tesāhaṃ puṭṭho akkhāmi,"
msgstr "When I’m asked, I explain to them"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:7.4"
msgid "yaṃ saccaṃ taṃ nirūpadhin”ti."
msgstr "the truth without attachments.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.124"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.272"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhante, gāmassa vā nigamassa vā avidūre pokkharaṇī."
msgstr "“Sir, suppose there was a lotus pond not far from a town or village,"

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.2"
msgid "Tatrassa kakkaṭako."
msgstr "and a crab lived there."

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā kumārakā vā kumārikāyo vā tamhā gāmā vā nigamā "
"vā nikkhamitvā yena sā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkameyyuṃ; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ "
"kakkaṭakaṃ udakā uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhapeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then several boys or girls would leave the town or village and go to the "
"pond, where they’d pull out the crab and put it on dry land."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-tortoises-and-samadhi/3020
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ yadeva hi so, bhante, kakkaṭako aḷaṃ abhininnāmeyya taṃ tadeva te "
"kumārakā vā kumārikāyo vā kaṭṭhena vā kathalāya vā sañchindeyyuṃ "
"sambhañjeyyuṃ sampalibhañjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Whenever that crab extended a claw, those boys or girls would snap, crack, "
"and break it off with a stick or a stone."

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.5"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhante, kakkaṭako sabbehi aḷehi sañchinnehi sambhaggehi "
"sampalibhaggehi abhabbo taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ otarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"And when that crab’s claws had all been snapped, cracked, and broken off it "
"wouldn’t be able to return down into that lotus pond."

#. VAR: bhante, yāni kānici visūkāyikāni → yāni visukāyikāni (bj, mr) | yāni kānici visukāyikāni (s1) | yānikānici visūkāyitāni (s2, s3) | yāni sukāyikāni (pts1)
#. VAR: vipphanditāni, sabbāni → kānici kānici sabbāni (bj, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.24:8.6"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhante, yāni kānici visūkāyikāni visevitāni vipphanditāni, "
"sabbāni tāni bhagavatā sañchinnāni sambhaggāni sampalibhaggāni."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, sir, the Buddha has snapped, cracked, and broken off all my "
"tricks, dodges, and evasions."

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.7"
msgid ""
"Abhabbo dānāhaṃ, bhante, puna bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamituṃ yadidaṃ "
"otārāpekkho”ti."
msgstr ""
"Now I’m not able to approach the Buddha again in hopes of finding a "
"vulnerability.”"

msgctxt "sn4.24:8.8"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato santike imā nibbejanīyā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked recited these verses of disappointment in the Buddha’s "
"presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.1"
msgid "“Medavaṇṇañca pāsāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "“A crow once circled a stone"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.2"
msgid "vāyaso anupariyagā;"
msgstr "that looked like a lump of fat."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.3"
msgid "Apettha muduṃ vindema,"
msgstr "‘Perhaps I’ll find something tender,’ it thought,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:9.4"
msgid "api assādanā siyā."
msgstr "‘perhaps there’s something tasty.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.1"
msgid "Aladdhā tattha assādaṃ,"
msgstr "But it didn’t find anything tasty,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.2"
msgid "vāyasetto apakkame;"
msgstr "so the crow left that place."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.3"
msgid "Kākova selamāsajja,"
msgstr "Like the crow that pecked the stone,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.24:10.4"
msgid "nibbijjāpema gotamā”ti."
msgstr "I leave Gotama disappointed.”"
